                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2151/39.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Spanish Chargé</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Memorandum.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 17, 1907</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Acting Secretary of State has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the
                    memorandum of the Spanish chargé d’affaires stating, under the instruction of
                    his Government, the action which the Governments of Spain and France have found
                    necessary to take in order to suppress the disturbances at Casablanca without
                    detriment to the integrity of Morocco and the sovereignty of the Sultan.</p>
                <p>The Government of the United States has taken due notice of the
                    communication.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
